00:25:30,178 --> 00:25:32,612
Some of them
are just marvelous people.

248
00:25:32,814 --> 00:25:36,807
Others walk through a pile and track
it through an investigation.

249
00:25:37,018 --> 00:25:39,179
You better change
your attitude fast.

250
00:25:39,387 --> 00:25:42,322
Because unless we
reach an agreement with them...

251
00:25:42,524 --> 00:25:46,119
...it's liable to cost this city
2 million, and your career.

252
00:25:48,296 --> 00:25:49,627
Join us, please.

253
00:25:49,831 --> 00:25:52,493
This is Ms. Samantha Walker
of station lKWSF.

254
00:25:52,701 --> 00:25:53,599
Captain Donnelly.

255
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:57,033
- Ms. Walker.
- Captain.

256
00:25:57,239 --> 00:26:00,072
- And this is Inspector--
- Callahan. We've met.

257
00:26:00,275 --> 00:26:03,574
Yes, of course. Won't you sit down?

258
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:06,636
Ms. Walker...

259
00:26:06,848 --> 00:26:10,944
... Lieutenant Ackerman tells me
you have a proposal to make...

260
00:26:11,152 --> 00:26:13,620
... regarding the accidental
damage to--

261
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:16,484
There was nothing accidental about it.

262
00:26:18,426 --> 00:26:21,293
The department might have something
to say about that.

263
00:26:21,496 --> 00:26:23,964
Although the camera was destroyed...

264
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:27,032
...I have the entire
incident on video.

265
00:26:28,570 --> 00:26:29,969
I see.

266
00:26:33,208 --> 00:26:34,368
And your proposal?

267
00:26:35,610 --> 00:26:39,239
We may be willing to drop
the lawsuit against the city...

268
00:26:39,447 --> 00:26:41,938
...but that depends
on Inspector Callahan.

269
00:26:43,918 --> 00:26:46,580
I'm sure the inspector
would be willing to--

270
00:26:46,788 --> 00:26:48,278
What do you have in mind?

271
00:26:50,859 --> 00:26:51,848
Dinner.

272
00:27:08,610 --> 00:27:10,976
I owe you an apology.

273
00:27:11,279 --> 00:27:13,713
You were right
about what I did the other day.

274
00:27:13,915 --> 00:27:17,407
I had no business intruding
on that girl's grief.

275
00:27:19,321 --> 00:27:20,879
I get too eager sometimes.

276
00:27:21,089 --> 00:27:24,183
In my rush to get the story,
I made an error in judgement.

277
00:27:24,392 --> 00:27:26,223
We all make those sometimes.

278
00:27:26,428 --> 00:27:28,896
No, I should have known better.

279
00:27:29,097 --> 00:27:30,655
I'm sorry.

280
00:27:31,766 --> 00:27:34,326
- Let me ask you, Miss Walker--
- Sam.

281
00:27:34,602 --> 00:27:35,694
Sam.

282
00:27:35,904 --> 00:27:36,928
Do you like cops?

283
00:27:38,006 --> 00:27:40,440
If they' re not in my
rear- view mirror. Why?

284
00:27:42,210 --> 00:27:44,474
I wonder what
we' re supposed to talk about...

285
00:27:44,679 --> 00:27:47,045
...other than the damaged camera.

286
00:27:47,248 --> 00:27:49,045
Oh, no, no, no.

287
00:27:49,250 --> 00:27:52,515
I'm letting the insurance company
deal with that.

288
00:27:53,655 --> 00:27:57,455
And I think I can be persuaded
to drop the lawsuit...

289
00:27:57,659 --> 00:27:59,559
...but I want something in return.

290
00:28:02,030 --> 00:28:03,122
What would that be?

291
00:28:03,465 --> 00:28:04,693
I want your story.

292
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:10,100
What's that?

293
00:28:10,305 --> 00:28:12,739
I've done my homework on you.

294
00:28:12,941 --> 00:28:15,375
You've had quite a colorful career.

295
00:28:15,577 --> 00:28:17,272
Loot at this. You see...

296
00:28:17,479 --> 00:28:21,677
...there's a lot of interest right now
in the Janero case...

297
00:28:21,883 --> 00:28:23,748
...and the cop who put him in prison.

298
00:28:23,952 --> 00:28:28,321
Channel 8 is doing a news special
on organized crime in the Bay Area.

299
00:28:28,523 --> 00:28:32,653
But what I would like to do
is an in- depth profile...

300
00:28:32,861 --> 00:28:35,762
...of you, Inspector Harry Callahan.

301
00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:37,556
Sorry, I'm not interested.

302
00:28:37,766 --> 00:28:41,896
Why not? This latest attempt
on your life by one of Janero's men--

303
00:28:42,103 --> 00:28:45,004
You' re not interested
in doing a story on me.

304
00:28:45,206 --> 00:28:47,174
You want blood. That's what sells--

305
00:28:47,375 --> 00:28:50,242
- Now wait a minute--
- No, you wait a minute.

306
00:28:50,445 --> 00:28:53,005
You people are interested
in death and mayhem...

307
00:28:53,214 --> 00:28:55,444
...and you don't care
how you get the story.

308
00:28:55,650 --> 00:28:59,984
That is not fair. That's not
the kind of journalism I do.

309
00:29:00,188 --> 00:29:02,816
To you I'm just a cop
with a price on his head.

310
00:29:03,024 --> 00:29:07,017
Let me tell you, I don't like
people saying they're gonna kill me.

311
00:29:07,228 --> 00:29:10,755
Nor do I like journalists using it
as a way to increase ratings.

312
00:29:10,965 --> 00:29:14,867
- What I was going to say--
- That's the end of the story.

313
00:29:31,085 --> 00:29:32,177
Sorry.

314
00:29:34,923 --> 00:29:37,221
The coroner's report last night...

315
00:29:37,725 --> 00:29:39,818
...said that Squares used speedballs.

316
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:41,689
Injecting cocaine and heroin?

317
00:29:41,896 --> 00:29:43,420
But that's not what killed him.

318
00:29:43,631 --> 00:29:46,794
He was using an inhaler
with some new designer drug.

319
00:29:47,001 --> 00:29:49,094
A synthetic form of heroin.

320
00:29:49,304 --> 00:29:52,068
You mean something along the lines
of China White.

321
00:29:52,273 --> 00:29:55,071
Only a thousand times wore powerful.

322
00:29:55,276 --> 00:29:58,507
One snort and he went into
immediate respiratory failure.

323
00:29:58,713 --> 00:30:00,408
IKnow what I'm trying to figure?

324
00:30:00,615 --> 00:30:02,276
Why is a guy like that...

325
00:30:02,484 --> 00:30:06,284
...screwing with synthetic junk
when he's got the real stuff?

326
00:30:06,488 --> 00:30:08,649
Maybe he didn't know
what he was using.

327
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:15,222
Harry.

328
00:30:20,201 --> 00:30:21,031
Harry?

329
00:30:23,638 --> 00:30:25,299
Sorry about that.

330
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:30,237
Get you next time.

331
00:30:36,784 --> 00:30:39,912
Check the cast and crew
for prior drug busts.

332
00:30:40,121 --> 00:30:44,888
I'll check with Narcotics to see if any
dealers are moving synthetic heroin.

333
00:30:45,193 --> 00:30:47,457
Harry, there's something here
you should see.

334
00:30:48,162 --> 00:30:51,131
A story to be published
in today's T ribune...

335
00:30:51,332 --> 00:30:55,462
...reveals that director Peter Swan
and several other people involved...

336
00:30:55,670 --> 00:31:00,539
...in the film Hotel Satan were
playing a game called "The Dead Pool. "

337
00:31:00,742 --> 00:31:03,267
According to sources,
the object of the game...

338
00:31:03,478 --> 00:31:06,379
... was for players to pick
eight Bay Area celebrities...

339
00:31:06,581 --> 00:31:10,244
... who might die
by a predetermined date.

340
00:31:10,451 --> 00:31:15,252
The winner was to possess the list
with the most dead celebrities.

341
00:31:15,456 --> 00:31:17,583
What makes this story significant...

342
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:22,786
...is that rock star Johnny Squares
was on director Peter Swan's list.

343
00:31:22,997 --> 00:31:25,795
Although Swan would not comment...

344
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,333
... we have confirmed that
there was such a game...

345
00:31:29,537 --> 00:31:34,099
...and Swan's production accountant,
Dean Madison, was also involved.

346
00:31:34,342 --> 00:31:36,902
Ironically, Madison was
killed yesterday...

347
00:31:37,111 --> 00:31:40,603
...in a tragic holdup attempt
that took place in Chinatown.

348
00:31:43,685 --> 00:31:47,985
"There is no man who is master of the
breath of life so as to retain it...

349
00:31:48,189 --> 00:31:51,181
...and none has mastery
over the day of death.

350
00:31:51,392 --> 00:31:54,225
For the Lord of all
shows no partiality...

351
00:31:54,429 --> 00:31:55,987
... nor does He fear greatness...

352
00:31:56,197 --> 00:31:58,062
... because He himself
made the great...

353
00:31:58,266 --> 00:31:59,790
...as well as the small.

354
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:02,799
And He provides for all alike.

355
00:32:03,571 --> 00:32:07,132
And the dust returns to the
earth, as it once was.

356
00:32:07,575 --> 00:32:11,170
And the life breath
returns to God, who gaveth. "

357
00:32:18,553 --> 00:32:20,282
My condolences.

358
00:32:20,955 --> 00:32:23,515
Mrs. Dayton, I'm terribly sorry.

359
00:32:23,758 --> 00:32:26,750
Suzanne, I'm very sorry
for your trouble.

360
00:32:26,961 --> 00:32:28,258
Thank you.

361
00:32:30,064 --> 00:32:31,554
My sympathies, dear.

362
00:32:34,102 --> 00:32:37,731
Do you mind, gentlemen?
I happen to be at a funeral.

363
00:32:37,972 --> 00:32:39,906
I'd like to talk about your list.

364
00:32:40,108 --> 00:32:43,566
It's no big secret.
The cast and crew knew about it.

365
00:32:43,778 --> 00:32:46,975
The Dead Pool is just a harmless game.

366
00:32:47,181 --> 00:32:49,547
It sounds pretty sick to me.

367
00:32:50,118 --> 00:32:51,608
Let me tell you something.

368
00:32:51,986 --> 00:32:54,921
People are fascinated
with death and violence.

369
00:32:55,123 --> 00:32:57,023
That's why my films make money.

370
00:32:57,225 --> 00:33:00,524
They're an escape,
a vicarious release of fear.

371
00:33:00,728 --> 00:33:02,559
Same thing with this game.

372
00:33:02,764 --> 00:33:05,460
Nobody takes my films
or the Dead Pool seriously.

373
00:33:06,167 --> 00:33:09,694
Someone gave Squares the drugs
that killed him. Maybe you.

374
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:13,362
You can't tie me to Johnny's death
because of a coincidence.

375
00:33:14,809 --> 00:33:19,075
My assistant and effects supervisor
played too. Why not talk to them?

376
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:20,247
We will.

377
00:33:21,215 --> 00:33:23,308
But nobody on their list is dead yet.

378
00:33:23,518 --> 00:33:28,012
Johnny was a drug user and I predicted
he'd die this year. That's all.

379
00:33:28,222 --> 00:33:31,316
The idea is to pick celebrities
who won't make it...

380
00:33:31,526 --> 00:33:34,552
... because they' re old, sick
or in a high- risk profession.

381
00:33:34,762 --> 00:33:36,252
Like police work?

382
00:33:36,731 --> 00:33:37,698
Nothing personal.

383
00:33:37,899 --> 00:33:40,459
I don't like being on your list, Swan.

384
00:33:40,668 --> 00:33:43,398
That's what this is really about,
isn't it?

385
00:33:43,604 --> 00:33:44,764
If you have a choice--

386
00:33:44,972 --> 00:33:47,668
Maybe I'll start my own Pool
and put you on it.

387
00:33:47,875 --> 00:33:49,308
Are you threatening me?

388
00:33:49,944 --> 00:33:54,347
If you want to play the game,
you'd better know the rules, love.

389
00:34:13,134 --> 00:34:15,261
That's our report. I'm Patrick Snow.

390
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:18,337
I'm Samantha Walker.
Thank you for being with us.

391
00:34:18,539 --> 00:34:20,507
Tune in tonight
for an exclusive report...

392
00:34:20,708 --> 00:34:23,108
...on chemical dependency
among celebrities.

393
00:34:23,311 --> 00:34:24,938
Who they are, why they do it...

394
00:34:25,146 --> 00:34:27,774
...and the price they pay.
Tonight at 11.

395
00:34:27,982 --> 00:34:29,279
Good night.

396
00:34:30,218 --> 00:34:31,845
And we' re clear.

397
00:34:50,671 --> 00:34:52,935
Thought I'd seen the last of you.

398
00:34:53,141 --> 00:34:54,665
I saw your report yesterday.

399
00:34:54,876 --> 00:34:57,003
We confirmed it
with people in the game.

400
00:34:57,211 --> 00:35:01,978
Vicky Owens, Swan's assistant,
and effects supervisor, Jeff Howser.

401
00:35:02,316 --> 00:35:05,149
It didn't occur to you
to clear it with us first?

402
00:35:05,353 --> 00:35:06,911
I had to go with the story.

403
00:35:07,121 --> 00:35:10,648
The papers got the same tip.
I had to get the story out fast.

404
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:13,053
Or someone else would get it first?

405
00:35:13,261 --> 00:35:15,491
- Something like that.
- How were you tipped?

406
00:35:15,696 --> 00:35:19,655
By mail. A copy of the Dead Pool
and a letter explaining it.

407
00:35:22,236 --> 00:35:24,568
- It's already started.
- What has?

408
00:35:24,772 --> 00:35:26,797
All the media bullshit.

409
00:35:27,041 --> 00:35:31,068
Newspapers print the Dead Pool
and it hurts our investigation.

410
00:35:31,279 --> 00:35:32,837
What bothers you...

411
00:35:33,047 --> 00:35:35,777
...is that we found out about
the Dead Pool first.

412
00:35:35,983 --> 00:35:40,352
You people take Janero and the Dead
Pool, add hype and distortion...

413
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:42,182
...and innocent people get hurt.

414
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:44,358
Aren't you overreacting?

415
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:45,992
I've seen it happen.

416
00:35:46,194 --> 00:35:49,027
I don't like the hype, either...

417
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:51,562
... but it happens when reporters
compete for a story.

418
00:35:51,933 --> 00:35:55,926
Why don't you start thinking about
your responsibility to the public?

419
00:35:57,438 --> 00:36:00,373
You can't kill the messenger
because of the message.

420
00:36:01,943 --> 00:36:06,277
I'm sorry, it wasn't my intention
to screw up your investigation.

421
00:36:07,181 --> 00:36:09,445
Here's the list. Now, excuse me.

422
00:36:11,986 --> 00:36:13,180
Thanks.

423
00:36:16,958 --> 00:36:18,482
It seems I owe you one.

424
00:36:21,495 --> 00:36:22,985
Dinner, that is.

425
00:36:26,167 --> 00:36:30,934
I was offered a job as an anchor
at this small, local station.

426
00:36:31,138 --> 00:36:32,571
Because...

427
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:36,037
... I was first runner- up
in Miss Colorado.

428
00:36:36,244 --> 00:36:38,838
Colorado? We' re right over here.

429
00:36:39,046 --> 00:36:43,449
But I had absolutely no experience,
just my bachelor's in journalism.

430
00:36:43,651 --> 00:36:47,519
But it was a way in, so I grabbed it.

431
00:36:50,658 --> 00:36:53,627
But I didn't just smile at
the camera and read copy.

432
00:36:53,828 --> 00:36:56,456
I did anything and everything
at this station.

433
00:36:56,664 --> 00:37:00,725
Sports, news, hard news, weather.

434
00:37:00,935 --> 00:37:02,869
I produced documentaries.

435
00:37:04,705 --> 00:37:06,639
I love San Francisco.

436
00:37:06,841 --> 00:37:08,468
But it isn't easy.

437
00:37:09,844 --> 00:37:12,005
Big city, big news.

438
00:37:12,914 --> 00:37:15,280
I had to prove myself all over again.

439
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:17,144
Have you succeeded?

440
00:37:17,518 --> 00:37:18,746
Somewhat.

441
00:37:20,087 --> 00:37:21,520
Apparently not with you.

442
00:37:22,790 --> 00:37:27,159
I shouldn't complain. At least you
stayed for dinner this time.

443
00:37:28,963 --> 00:37:31,124
I'd still love to do your story.

444
00:37:31,699 --> 00:37:32,961
No, thanks.

445
00:37:33,234 --> 00:37:36,533
You're wrong about me, Callahan,
and what I want to do.

446
00:37:37,305 --> 00:37:39,239
I wish I could convince you.

447
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:41,073
I'll tell you what.

448
00:37:41,676 --> 00:37:43,303
Let's think on it.

449
00:37:44,412 --> 00:37:45,310
Sounds fair.

450
00:37:48,049 --> 00:37:49,277
Thank you.

451
00:38:03,898 --> 00:38:07,163
It's the truth,
I don't care what you say.

452
00:38:14,141 --> 00:38:15,768
Hey, Callahan.

453
00:38:16,143 --> 00:38:18,703
- You' re Callahan, aren't you?
- That's right.

454
00:38:18,913 --> 00:38:20,005
What can I do for you?

455
00:38:20,214 --> 00:38:22,614
You' re the cop who put Janero away.

456
00:38:25,653 --> 00:38:28,213
All I want is your autograph.

457
00:38:29,991 --> 00:38:31,822
Can I shake your hand?

458
00:38:35,429 --> 00:38:36,896
I'd just like to thank you.

459
00:38:37,098 --> 00:38:40,397
It's about time somebody
did something about Janero.

460
00:38:40,601 --> 00:38:44,367
Could you sign it to
Chester Docksteder? That's me.

461
00:38:45,473 --> 00:38:46,872
Let me buy you a drink.

462
00:38:47,074 --> 00:38:48,541
Some other time.

463
00:38:49,143 --> 00:38:52,806
We need more cops like you.
That's what we need.

464
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:55,575
I gotta change my shorts.

465
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:01,049
What are you laughing at?

466
00:39:01,255 --> 00:39:03,985
This is your 15 minutes, Callahan.

467
00:39:04,525 --> 00:39:08,985
Andy Warhol said everybody's famous
for 15 minutes. Well, this is it.

468
00:39:09,196 --> 00:39:10,220
Swell.

469
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,604
Was it your first autograph?

470
00:39:27,815 --> 00:39:28,975
Yeah.

471
00:39:29,250 --> 00:39:31,411
And I hope my last.

472
00:40:58,205 --> 00:40:59,934
You know something?

473
00:41:00,207 --> 00:41:03,142
I don't think Lou Janero
likes you very much.

474
00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:17,785
She's okay. Just a little shaken up.

475
00:41:23,964 --> 00:41:25,625
How're you doing, girl?

476
00:41:29,336 --> 00:41:33,102
Whatever they're paying you, Harry,
it couldn't be enough.

477
00:41:37,678 --> 00:41:39,202
My colleagues.

478
00:41:44,318 --> 00:41:46,218
I don't want to be the news.

479
00:41:47,888 --> 00:41:49,480
Let's get you out of here.

480
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:24,591
You sure you want to see this guy?

481
00:42:24,792 --> 00:42:26,054
Yeah.

482
00:42:36,837 --> 00:42:38,134
Here's your animal.

483
00:42:38,672 --> 00:42:39,502
Hicks.

484
00:42:39,707 --> 00:42:41,334
What the fuck do you want?

485
00:42:41,542 --> 00:42:43,601
I brought you some cigarettes.

486
00:42:44,211 --> 00:42:46,441
And what would I have to do for you?

487
00:42:46,714 --> 00:42:49,683
Nothing. Just stand where I tell you.

488
00:43:16,243 --> 00:43:17,574
Stay right here.

489
00:43:17,778 --> 00:43:19,245
Fifth cell down.

490
00:43:28,355 --> 00:43:32,348
That's the trouble with this prison.
They let anybody in.

491
00:43:32,793 --> 00:43:35,853
I don't like scum like you
trying to kill me.

492
00:43:37,131 --> 00:43:41,966
Sounds to me like this Dead Pool thing
is making you a little paranoid.

493
00:43:43,537 --> 00:43:46,233
Oh, yeah. I heard about it.

494
00:43:46,473 --> 00:43:49,135
Good news travels fast.

495
00:43:49,343 --> 00:43:51,709
Big fucking media hero.

496
00:43:51,912 --> 00:43:54,437
Hero today and gone tomorrow.

497
00:43:54,715 --> 00:43:56,683
Call off your guns.

498
00:43:56,917 --> 00:43:58,578
