01:04:41,727 --> 01:04:43,251
How y'all doing?

754
01:04:59,512 --> 01:05:01,605
You' re the last asshole Janero sends.

755
01:05:01,814 --> 01:05:03,145
Wait, you got it wrong!

756
01:05:03,349 --> 01:05:06,682
Don't fuck with me, buddy.
I'll kick your ass right now.

757
01:05:06,886 --> 01:05:08,114
It's not what you think.

758
01:05:08,321 --> 01:05:10,289
Janero did hire us.

759
01:05:10,489 --> 01:05:12,354
But this ain't a hit.

760
01:05:12,558 --> 01:05:16,221
Janero doesn't want
anything to happen to you.

761
01:05:16,429 --> 01:05:17,361
We're your...

762
01:05:18,264 --> 01:05:19,356
... bodyguards.

763
01:05:30,176 --> 01:05:32,940
Those letters
all came from your files.

764
01:05:33,346 --> 01:05:35,871
Harlan Rook. God.

765
01:05:36,082 --> 01:05:37,447
Yes, I remember him.

766
01:05:37,650 --> 01:05:42,144
Every time I was at a film festival
or a seminar, he was there.

767
01:05:42,355 --> 01:05:46,587
Mr. I Know- It- All, I called him.
He knew everything about my films.

768
01:05:48,094 --> 01:05:51,530
To tell the truth,
I found it a little unnerving.

769
01:05:52,398 --> 01:05:53,888
What'd he want?

770
01:05:54,700 --> 01:05:55,997
He had this screenplay...

771
01:05:56,202 --> 01:05:58,397
...for a horror film
he wanted me to direct.

772
01:05:58,604 --> 01:06:01,300
He said it'd be
the ultimate Peter Swan film.

773
01:06:01,507 --> 01:06:03,475
He was crazy.
I couldn't get rid of him.

774
01:06:03,676 --> 01:06:07,168
Finally, my attorney
put a restraining order on him.

775
01:06:07,380 --> 01:06:08,574
Then what happened?

776
01:06:08,781 --> 01:06:10,874
I didn't see or hear from him again.

777
01:06:11,083 --> 01:06:13,950
That must have been over a year ago.

778
01:06:15,388 --> 01:06:16,355
Is he the one?

779
01:06:16,555 --> 01:06:18,785
The typewriter
used on these letters...

780
01:06:18,991 --> 01:06:22,518
...is the same one used
to tip us off to the Dead Pool.

781
01:06:27,133 --> 01:06:30,432
Call Swan's attorney
and see what he knows about Rook.

782
01:06:30,636 --> 01:06:32,433
And run a DMV check.

783
01:06:32,638 --> 01:06:33,764
Right.

784
01:07:01,567 --> 01:07:05,833
It might not be a bad idea to start
playing it a little safe.

785
01:07:06,038 --> 01:07:08,233
Maybe your granddaddy can paint me up.

786
01:07:08,441 --> 01:07:10,306
Look, I'm being serious.

787
01:07:10,509 --> 01:07:14,445
Don't go where you normally go,
not even home. You can stay with me.

788
01:07:14,914 --> 01:07:18,077
Thanks, but I think I can
do a little better.

789
01:07:28,961 --> 01:07:30,485
Price of fame.

790
01:08:00,726 --> 01:08:04,253
Is this what Ackerman meant
by cooperating with the press?

791
01:08:04,463 --> 01:08:07,864
It must have been one of those
in- depth interviews.

792
01:08:18,778 --> 01:08:21,941
I got a lead on Rook.
A psychiatrist who treated him.

793
01:08:22,148 --> 01:08:23,376
Good.

794
01:08:26,452 --> 01:08:27,544
- Give it a try.
- Okay.

795
01:08:32,925 --> 01:08:35,985
It won't respond.
Someone's on my frequency.

796
01:08:49,141 --> 01:08:51,701
Forget it. It's just not working.

797
01:09:22,208 --> 01:09:24,073
Now what the hell is that?

798
01:12:43,042 --> 01:12:45,101
Time's up, Callahan.

799
01:13:22,548 --> 01:13:24,106
You all right, Al?

800
01:13:24,483 --> 01:13:26,007
Shit.

801
01:13:39,064 --> 01:13:40,656
Two fractured ribs.

802
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:44,192
He bled in the chest.
We drained it and set up an IV.

803
01:13:44,403 --> 01:13:48,169
He's lucky, the bulletproof vest
he had on saved his life.

804
01:13:49,041 --> 01:13:51,635
Another of my
grandfather's superstitions.

805
01:13:51,844 --> 01:13:53,903
When your partner gives you advice...

806
01:13:54,113 --> 01:13:55,080
...take it.

807
01:13:56,315 --> 01:13:57,782
Harry.

808
01:14:06,358 --> 01:14:10,192
This is Dr. Friedman, chief
psychiatrist here at the hospital.

809
01:14:10,395 --> 01:14:12,056
I'm sorry about what happened.

810
01:14:12,264 --> 01:14:14,061
I feel somewhat responsible.

811
01:14:14,266 --> 01:14:17,394
Your partner contacted me about
a former patient of ours.

812
01:14:17,603 --> 01:14:19,127
- Harlan Rook?
- Yes.

813
01:14:19,338 --> 01:14:23,001
At first, I didn't recall the name.
I found the file today.

814
01:14:23,775 --> 01:14:25,868
He was evaluated here a year ago.

815
01:14:26,078 --> 01:14:28,546
The diagnosis was
process schizophrenia.

816
01:14:28,747 --> 01:14:30,180
Multiple personality.

817
01:14:30,382 --> 01:14:31,212
Exactly.

818
01:14:31,884 --> 01:14:33,852
His sense of self- hate
was so strong...

819
01:14:34,052 --> 01:14:37,146
...that he no longer had
any personality of his own.

820
01:14:37,356 --> 01:14:40,814
Consequently,
he substituted identities...

821
01:14:41,026 --> 01:14:43,494
...found in books, films...

822
01:14:43,695 --> 01:14:45,128
...fan magazines.

823
01:14:45,330 --> 01:14:48,356
Identities with which he had
love- hate relationships.

824
01:14:48,567 --> 01:14:50,933
He wasn't dangerous enough to hold?

825
01:14:51,136 --> 01:14:54,537
Most mentally ill people
are not violent, inspector.

826
01:14:54,740 --> 01:14:59,404
By law, a person who poses no danger
can only be held for 72 hours.

827
01:15:00,445 --> 01:15:04,245
I'm sorry, this is one instance
where the system failed.

828
01:15:04,449 --> 01:15:06,212
Is this address recent?

829
01:15:06,418 --> 01:15:07,851
I assume it's still the same.

830
01:15:11,957 --> 01:15:13,151
Samantha Walker.

831
01:15:13,358 --> 01:15:15,417
This is Peter Swan, Ms. Walker.

832
01:15:15,627 --> 01:15:18,460
Your coverage of my predicament
has been thorough...

833
01:15:18,664 --> 01:15:22,156
...but my side hasn't been told
as well as it could be.

834
01:15:22,367 --> 01:15:23,629
I see.

835
01:15:23,835 --> 01:15:26,963
I'm prepared to grant you
an exclusive interview.

836
01:15:27,172 --> 01:15:29,072
Are you interested?

837
01:15:33,979 --> 01:15:35,446
No doubt about it.

838
01:15:35,647 --> 01:15:36,978
He's our boy, Harry.

839
01:15:37,182 --> 01:15:40,310
Explosives. Caps.

840
01:15:40,519 --> 01:15:41,645
Detonator.

841
01:15:41,853 --> 01:15:42,911
It all connects.

842
01:15:43,488 --> 01:15:45,456
Harry, you gotta see this.

843
01:15:50,329 --> 01:15:51,990
Talk about obsession.

844
01:16:08,680 --> 01:16:12,377
Looks like he had a real
Peter Swan shrine going here.

845
01:16:15,153 --> 01:16:17,018
I'm not sure.

846
01:16:17,222 --> 01:16:19,622
I could have sworn I put it in my bag.

847
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:21,884
But I'm not sure.

848
01:16:22,094 --> 01:16:25,621
- Bob, do you have my little mike?
- It's in your bag.

849
01:16:25,831 --> 01:16:27,230
Thank you.

850
01:17:05,804 --> 01:17:06,964
Look at this.

851
01:17:10,008 --> 01:17:12,169
I'll call the TV station.

852
01:17:24,389 --> 01:17:28,291
Samantha went out to the shipyard
to interview Peter Swan.

853
01:17:28,493 --> 01:17:30,586
Swan doesn't know anything about it.

854
01:17:30,796 --> 01:17:33,026
- What's this?
- A payroll stub.

855
01:17:33,231 --> 01:17:36,530
Sundown Security, made out to
Ed Butler? I don't get it.

856
01:17:36,735 --> 01:17:40,466
That's the company that provides
security for Swan's locations.

857
01:17:40,672 --> 01:17:43,368
Ed Butler may be an alias for Rook.

858
01:17:43,575 --> 01:17:45,702
Where are you going? Harry?

859
01:17:45,911 --> 01:17:47,640
Harry!

860
01:17:47,846 --> 01:17:49,711
That's my car!

861
01:17:57,689 --> 01:17:58,519
Yes.

862
01:17:58,724 --> 01:18:00,624
That's the shot I'm looking for.

863
01:18:12,137 --> 01:18:13,934
What is it you want from me?

864
01:18:14,139 --> 01:18:16,505
You've got it wrong, love.

865
01:18:17,142 --> 01:18:19,167
This is what you wanted.

866
01:18:19,478 --> 01:18:22,242
An exclusive interview.

867
01:18:23,148 --> 01:18:24,410
But you' re not Swan.

868
01:18:24,616 --> 01:18:26,641
Shut up! You don't know!

869
01:18:26,852 --> 01:18:28,979
You don't know!

870
01:18:29,821 --> 01:18:31,516
I know who I am.

871
01:18:32,190 --> 01:18:33,623
Do you know who you are?

872
01:18:34,025 --> 01:18:34,855
Do you?!

873
01:18:35,060 --> 01:18:36,425
Yes.

874
01:18:36,795 --> 01:18:38,262
All those films he made.

875
01:18:38,463 --> 01:18:40,658
Those are my nightmares, not his!

876
01:18:41,433 --> 01:18:45,494
Every night I dream,
and somehow he reads my mind.

877
01:18:45,704 --> 01:18:47,865
He stole my thoughts.

878
01:18:48,073 --> 01:18:52,669
He put my thoughts on film,
and he takes all the credit.

879
01:18:54,780 --> 01:18:56,805
He can't get away with it.

880
01:18:59,451 --> 01:19:01,248
He has to pay.

881
01:19:07,392 --> 01:19:09,519
He stole my nightmares
and made them real.

882
01:19:09,728 --> 01:19:11,593
So I stole his Dead Pool.

883
01:19:12,097 --> 01:19:14,691
I'll play his game and make it real.

884
01:19:17,235 --> 01:19:18,930
He can take credit for that.

885
01:20:44,823 --> 01:20:45,755
Drop it, Rook.

886
01:20:45,957 --> 01:20:50,189
You didn't die, Callahan,
so I had to find another celebrity.

887
01:20:54,699 --> 01:20:55,597
You're next.

888
01:20:55,800 --> 01:20:58,234
Shoot me, Callahan.

889
01:20:58,436 --> 01:20:59,994
Maybe you'll get lucky.

890
01:21:00,205 --> 01:21:04,164
Maybe my muscles won't contract
and drive this knife into her throat.

891
01:21:05,744 --> 01:21:06,768
Let her go.

892
01:21:07,612 --> 01:21:08,909
First the gun.

893
01:21:09,114 --> 01:21:11,241
Drop it and kick it over to me.

894
01:21:15,353 --> 01:21:17,082
Time's up. What's it gonna be?

895
01:21:25,697 --> 01:21:26,959
What the fuck?

896
01:21:31,836 --> 01:21:34,168
You've locked yourself in, asshole.

897
01:21:34,706 --> 01:21:36,105
Yeah.

898
01:21:36,308 --> 01:21:38,105
Just you and me, asshole.

899
01:21:40,845 --> 01:21:42,278
The gun, Callahan.

900
01:21:44,149 --> 01:21:44,979
Now!

901
01:21:45,183 --> 01:21:46,047
No!

902
01:21:46,251 --> 01:21:47,946
He'll kill us both!

903
01:21:50,655 --> 01:21:52,020
Oh, God.

904
01:22:02,233 --> 01:22:05,999
You let me down,
Mr. Famous- Fucking- Cop.

905
01:22:06,371 --> 01:22:08,032
You let Swan get away.

906
01:22:08,239 --> 01:22:09,831
You're the killer, not Swan.

907
01:22:10,141 --> 01:22:11,870
I should have killed you first.

908
01:22:12,077 --> 01:22:14,045
That was my big mistake.

909
01:22:14,346 --> 01:22:15,643
Now kick it over to me.

910
01:22:17,515 --> 01:22:19,483
Harry, don't.

911
01:22:28,393 --> 01:22:29,951
Think you're smart, don't you?

912
01:22:47,145 --> 01:22:49,010
Callahan, you son of a bitch!

913
01:22:54,986 --> 01:22:56,817
I'm gonna kill you slow!

914
01:23:01,960 --> 01:23:03,951
Do you hear that, Callahan?!

915
01:24:20,805 --> 01:24:22,534
Stay in there.

916
01:25:31,743 --> 01:25:33,608
Callahan!

917
01:25:41,219 --> 01:25:43,414
Come on out, Callahan.

918
01:25:56,234 --> 01:25:58,600
There's nowhere left to run, Callahan.

919
01:25:59,537 --> 01:26:01,562
Don't make me come in and get you.

920
01:26:05,410 --> 01:26:07,037
The game's over!

921
01:26:07,245 --> 01:26:08,610
You' re out of bullets.

922
01:26:38,443 --> 01:26:40,035
You know what that means.

923
01:26:42,146 --> 01:26:43,545
You' re shit out of luck.

924
01:27:28,726 --> 01:27:31,627
- Where's Rook?
- He's hanging out back there.

925
01:27:37,101 --> 01:27:40,002
Inspector, was this another
hit attempt by Janero?

926
01:27:40,204 --> 01:27:42,764
Is it connected to the Dead Pool case?

